Thank you, awesome!

So, first question about ERC1155.
 I would like to allow my users to send an ERC1155 id to several addresses at the same time (with an amount to be specified by addresses)

the "quick and easy way" would be to do something like this:

```js
    /**
     * @dev allows to transfer one id to several address 
     */
    function safeBatchTransferIdFrom(
        address from,
        address[] memory tos,
        uint256 id,
        uint256[] memory amounts,
        bytes memory data
    ) public virtual {
        require(
            tos.length == amounts.length,
            "ERC1155: recipients and amounts length mismatch"
        );

        for (uint256 i = 0; i < tos.length; i++) {
            safeTransferFrom(from, tos[i], id, amounts[i], data);
        }
    }
```

this is clearly not optimized, as it would emit a TransferSingle (and do all the safeTransferFrom verification) for every recipient.
But that would still cost less than doing 10 separate transactions if i'm not mistaken. And on Matic the cost is almost negligeable.

Any thoughts?

